## Jared Yorke - Facilities Manager

Jared brings years of experience and skills that will be vital to maintaining and improving the camp facilities as well as an excitement to invest in the lives of our campers and staff. After working in appliance repair and owning his own business in Ft. Wayne, IN, Jared and his family have sensed a clear call to transition into vocational ministry at Bear Lake Camp. Beyond overseeing the care of the camp physical plant, Jared has a passion for mentoring and teaching young people that will be a wonderful asset as he leads our LIT program.

Jared and his wife, Emme, have 4 children: Judah, Solomon, Ephraim, and Jubilee. He is an avid apiarist, keeping several hives and harvesting honey; a versatile musician; and a lover of Honda engines.
{% /twoColumns %}

---

{% twoColumns reverseOnMobile=true %}
## Karli Harlan - Food Service Director/Guest Group Coordinator

Karli joins the BLC staff team after being around camp for the last 15 years! From being a member of the BLC Summer Staff while attending college at Indiana Wesleyan University to being a "staff spouse" for the last 10+ years, Karli is well acquainted with the mission of Bear Lake! Karli's role at camp is to oversee all food service for BLC (building on a long tradition of "camp food is the best food") and rental programs and to ensure that all of our guest groups throughout the year have an exceptional experience at BLC from the first inquiry email to the (hopeful) rebooking for the next event. When she's not busy at camp, Karli loves being a mom to her three kids: Cooper, Owen, and Annie as well as discovering new and delicious foods that she enjoys sharing with others.

Karli earned her BSN from Indiana Wesleyan University in 2014.

